WEBVTT

00:01.015 --> 00:02.015
Narrator: Sugar,

00:02.017 --> 00:04.013
spice...

00:04.015 --> 00:06.010
And everything nice.

00:06.012 --> 00:08.005
These were
the ingredients chosen

00:08.007 --> 00:10.005
to create
the perfect little girl.

00:10.007 --> 00:12.018
But Professor Utonium
accidentally added

00:12.020 --> 00:14.013
an extra ingredient
to the concoction--

00:14.015 --> 00:16.010
Chemical "X."

00:16.012 --> 00:19.022
[Explosion]

00:19.024 --> 00:22.015
Thus the Powerpuff Girls
were born!

00:22.017 --> 00:24.010
Using their ultra-superpowers,

00:24.012 --> 00:28.007
Blossom, Bubbles, and Buttercup
have dedicated their lives

00:28.009 --> 00:31.028
to fighting crime
and the forces of evil!

00:32.000 --> 00:39.025
♪

00:39.027 --> 00:47.021
♪

00:47.023 --> 00:55.018
♪

00:55.020 --> 01:03.016
♪

01:05.005 --> 01:14.000
♪

01:16.011 --> 01:17.014
Narrator:
The city of Townsville,

01:17.016 --> 01:19.001
and it's a beautiful day.

01:19.003 --> 01:21.008
But not as beautiful
as it will be this Sunday,

01:21.010 --> 01:22.023
because it's Father's Day.

01:22.025 --> 01:24.029
And boy,
I can't wait.

01:25.001 --> 01:26.013
These little guys
are gonna hatch.

01:26.015 --> 01:29.003
Yes, everyone is excited
and getting ready,

01:29.005 --> 01:31.021
even Professor Utonium
and the Powerpuff Girls.

01:31.023 --> 01:35.011
Oh, girls, Father's Day is
my favorite holiday.

01:35.013 --> 01:36.005
Bubbles: Why?

01:36.007 --> 01:37.013
Well, if it weren't
for you,

01:37.015 --> 01:39.014
I wouldn't be able to
celebrate it.

01:39.016 --> 01:41.002
Blossom: Speaking
of celebration,

01:41.004 --> 01:42.023
what are you making
this year?

01:42.025 --> 01:47.016
Mmm. My favorite--
liver and onions.

01:48.005 --> 01:49.008
[Whispering
indistinctly]

01:49.010 --> 01:51.016
Well, what do you want
for a present?

01:51.018 --> 01:55.006
Oh, girls, anything you make me
will be fantastic.

01:55.008 --> 01:59.015
Besides, you know I don't need
material possessions.

01:59.017 --> 02:00.021
I've got you.

02:00.023 --> 02:03.013
I remember last year, Blossom,
you made me that--

02:03.015 --> 02:04.014
Blossom:
Ceramic bowl?

02:04.016 --> 02:07.000
Ceramic bowl.
Yeah. That was great.

02:07.002 --> 02:09.027
And Bubbles,
with your, uh, uh...

02:09.029 --> 02:11.005
What did you make me?

02:11.007 --> 02:12.008
Crayon drawling.

02:12.010 --> 02:15.021
Crayon drawling.
That was wonderful.

02:15.023 --> 02:16.027
And Buttercup--

02:16.029 --> 02:17.028
Boxing gloves!

02:18.000 --> 02:21.001
Oh, that's right--
made out of socks.

02:21.003 --> 02:22.027
I remember that.

02:22.029 --> 02:26.001
You see, girls, those gifts are
kind of funky,

02:26.003 --> 02:30.008
but they're charming, and, well,
that's all I really ne--

02:30.010 --> 02:32.012
Blossom:
Professor?

02:38.002 --> 02:40.011
What's the matter?!

02:41.006 --> 02:43.001
Look.

02:44.010 --> 02:47.022
The Pro Excellence
2000 golf clubs.

02:47.024 --> 02:50.029
Only 12 of these sets
exist in the whole world.

02:51.001 --> 02:54.028
Oh, my game would be perfect
if I had these.

02:55.000 --> 02:57.002
Oh, my, they are
beautiful--

02:57.004 --> 03:00.004
a true marvel of
craftsmanshi--

03:00.006 --> 03:01.005
Oh, dear!

03:01.007 --> 03:03.012
No wonder they're called
the 2000 Clubs.

03:03.014 --> 03:04.013
I can't afford
these.

03:04.015 --> 03:07.026
Oh, never mind.
Come on, girls.

03:07.028 --> 03:12.023
We'd better get home before
the liver spoils.

03:15.019 --> 03:16.027
All right, girls.

03:16.029 --> 03:19.004
That's the last of
the finishing touches.

03:19.006 --> 03:23.012
Bubbles: The Pro Excellence
2000 golf clubs!

03:23.014 --> 03:25.020
Buttercup:
These stink.

03:25.022 --> 03:29.014
Come on.
Back to the drawing board.

03:31.006 --> 03:32.027
Look, girls,
we're just not going to be

03:32.029 --> 03:35.006
able to raise enough money
by Father's Day.

03:35.008 --> 03:36.025
If we had some <i>real</i><i>talent,</i>

03:36.027 --> 03:39.007
we could raise money,
but we don't.

03:39.009 --> 03:41.003
Fighting crime's
a talent.

03:41.005 --> 03:42.003
[Buzzer]

03:42.005 --> 03:44.005
I'll get it!
Hello, Mayor.

03:44.007 --> 03:46.007
Blossom,
I need your help.

03:46.009 --> 03:48.020
Mojo Jojo is
destroying the town!

03:48.022 --> 03:50.008
We're on our way!

03:50.010 --> 03:53.010
Girls, we <i>can</i><i>raise</i>
that money!

03:53.012 --> 03:56.003
[Siren]

03:59.008 --> 04:00.009
Blossom:
All right, Mojo,

04:00.011 --> 04:03.006
how do you explain yourself
this time?

04:03.008 --> 04:05.000
The hobby store did not
have what I wanted,

04:05.002 --> 04:06.009
so I lost my temper.

04:06.011 --> 04:07.014
Oh, come on!

04:07.016 --> 04:09.029
I was looking for
a model ship to build.

04:10.001 --> 04:10.029
It is my hobby.

04:11.001 --> 04:12.019
Take him away,
boys!

04:12.021 --> 04:13.027
Our pleasure,
Blossom.

04:13.029 --> 04:17.022
Mayor: Girls, thank you
once again for saving the day.

04:17.024 --> 04:20.011
I know there are other things
you could be doing

04:20.013 --> 04:23.025
on a Saturday,
but crime never sleeps.

04:23.027 --> 04:26.023
We don't mind.
It's our special talent.

04:26.025 --> 04:27.028
Right, girls?

04:28.000 --> 04:28.029
Right.
Right.

04:29.001 --> 04:30.014
Ho ho! That's the spirit!

04:30.016 --> 04:33.017
And special talents
should be rewarded.

04:33.019 --> 04:36.019
Would you girls like
some cookies?

04:36.021 --> 04:39.002
Hmm...no, thanks.
We're not hungry.

04:39.004 --> 04:41.002
Oh, but they're fresh.

04:41.004 --> 04:42.003
No, thanks.

04:42.005 --> 04:44.003
Well, I'd like to
repay you somehow.

04:44.005 --> 04:47.012
Well, actually,
me and the girls were talking,

04:47.014 --> 04:50.014
and we'd like to be
paid for our services.

04:50.016 --> 04:52.024
Ho ho! That's the spirit!

04:52.026 --> 04:55.016
You're very enterprising
little ladies.

04:55.018 --> 05:00.014
Well, I think I've got a few
nickels here in my change purse.

05:00.016 --> 05:02.003
What are
you charging, girls?

05:02.005 --> 05:03.019
Girls: $2,000.

05:03.021 --> 05:05.009
Oh, that's reasonable.

05:05.011 --> 05:08.029
Let's see. Here's 15 cents.

05:09.001 --> 05:13.027
Here's a--$2,000?!

05:13.029 --> 05:21.014
[Screaming]

05:21.016 --> 05:22.011
Ooh!
Ooh!
Ooh!

05:22.013 --> 05:26.010
Oh! Miss Bellum,
my heart pills.

05:26.012 --> 05:28.024
Sir, I think
these little ladies

05:28.026 --> 05:30.010
were just having
some fun.

05:30.012 --> 05:31.012
Fun nothing!

05:31.014 --> 05:33.027
Look,
I'm no sugar daddy.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.020
Those days are over.

05:36.022 --> 05:39.022
Girls, I think
you'd better run along

05:39.024 --> 05:42.022
and go clean up
Mojo's mess.

05:42.024 --> 05:45.017
Girls: Oh, all right.

05:54.002 --> 05:55.022
Uggggh!

05:58.000 --> 05:59.028
[Gasps]

06:03.018 --> 06:08.024
My life would be perfect
if I had a pair of these.

06:08.026 --> 06:12.016
♪

06:12.018 --> 06:16.003
Go on.
No one's looking.

06:18.011 --> 06:20.001
Attagirl!

06:21.015 --> 06:23.022
Narrator:
Well, ladies and gentlemen,

06:23.024 --> 06:27.020
I guess there's a first time
for everything.

06:28.025 --> 06:31.029
But with a new day,
perhaps there's hope.

06:32.001 --> 06:34.018
[Snoring]

06:35.024 --> 06:36.029
Happy Father's Day!

06:37.001 --> 06:40.014
Hey, shut up! Can't you see
I'm trying to--oh.

06:40.016 --> 06:41.014
Oh!

06:41.016 --> 06:43.025
What do you know, folks?
I'm a daddy.

06:43.027 --> 06:45.024
Professor: Ooh, girls,
something sure smells good.

06:45.026 --> 06:48.005
I hope you didn't go to
too much trouble.

06:48.007 --> 06:49.013
Buttercup: We don't mind.
We just wish

06:49.015 --> 06:51.018
we could have got you
those golf clubs.

06:51.020 --> 06:52.024
Oh, girls,
I don't need--

06:52.026 --> 06:54.024
Bubbles: Okay, you can open
your eyes now.

06:54.026 --> 06:56.020
Bubbles and Buttercup:
Happy Father's Day!

06:56.022 --> 06:59.002
Oh, my heavens! Brownies!

06:59.004 --> 07:01.012
Hey, wait.
Those aren't brownies.

07:01.014 --> 07:03.026
No. It's liver
and onions.

07:03.028 --> 07:05.021
Uhh.

07:06.014 --> 07:07.027
It's your favorite.

07:07.029 --> 07:09.010
Don't you
want any?

07:09.012 --> 07:13.003
I-I'd love some, b-but I can't
eat without all of you here.

07:13.005 --> 07:15.011
Yeah. What's taking Blossom
so long?

07:15.013 --> 07:18.002
Oh, she said she had
a special surprise.

07:18.004 --> 07:20.021
She didn't even want to
help with breakfast.

07:20.023 --> 07:23.001
Blossom:
Ladies and gentlemen!

07:23.003 --> 07:28.016
May I present the Father's Day
gift extraordinaire!

07:28.018 --> 07:31.007
For my favorite person
in the whole world,

07:31.009 --> 07:35.004
happy Father's Day!

07:38.012 --> 07:42.018
Aah! The Pro Excellence 2000
golf clubs!

07:42.020 --> 07:44.023
Aah! Aaaahhhh!

07:44.025 --> 07:46.001
Oh, thank you!

07:46.003 --> 07:48.001
Aaahhhh! Oh!

07:48.003 --> 07:51.009
Oh, thank you
so much, girls.

07:51.011 --> 07:54.005
Oh, no. This gift
is just from me.

07:54.007 --> 07:56.004
This is
my special present.

07:56.006 --> 07:57.024
Oh, how sweet.

07:57.026 --> 07:58.027
Wait a minute.

07:58.029 --> 08:00.017
How in the heck
did you get those?

08:00.019 --> 08:02.004
Who cares
how she got them?

08:02.006 --> 08:05.004
Oh, happy
Father's Day indeed!

08:05.006 --> 08:08.014
Oh, Blossom, this is
the best gift ever.

08:08.016 --> 08:09.016
Oh!

08:09.018 --> 08:10.019
You know why?

08:10.021 --> 08:12.021
Because I have a game
today with the Mayor,

08:12.023 --> 08:15.000
and I'm gonna win
with these babies!

08:15.002 --> 08:17.017
But where'd you get the
money
to buy them?

08:17.019 --> 08:20.005
Don't you mind
your sisters, Blossom.

08:20.007 --> 08:21.022
Girls,
money is no object.

08:21.024 --> 08:24.000
Now, if you don't mind,
I'm gonna go outside

08:24.002 --> 08:27.005
and try
these beauties out.

08:27.007 --> 08:28.026
Aren't you gonna eat
your breakfast?

08:28.028 --> 08:32.026
Oh, uh, just wrap that up
for me, honey.

08:35.022 --> 08:39.003
All right, Blossom, you've got
some explaining to do.

08:39.005 --> 08:42.017
Where the heck did you
get those clubs?

08:43.014 --> 08:45.006
I found them.

08:46.029 --> 08:49.001
Mayor: Can you
believe this, Chief?

08:49.003 --> 08:53.000
The rare Pro Excellence 2000
golf clubs

08:53.002 --> 08:55.025
mysteriously
disappeared.

08:55.027 --> 08:57.001
Hmm.
That's peculiar.

08:57.003 --> 09:00.011
Yeah. It happened right after
Mojo tore up the town.

09:00.013 --> 09:02.011
I say, do you think
he took them?

09:02.013 --> 09:05.001
Nah. Little monkeys
are too dumb to golf.

09:05.003 --> 09:07.020
But whoever did take them
is one lucky guy.

09:07.022 --> 09:10.007
I'll say. If I only had
a pair of these,

09:10.009 --> 09:12.026
my game
would be perfect.

09:12.028 --> 09:14.000
Me, too.

09:14.002 --> 09:15.025
Professor: Me fore!

09:15.027 --> 09:19.025
Are you boys ready to be beaten
by a real pro?

09:19.027 --> 09:20.020
Ha ha ha!

09:20.022 --> 09:23.012
Well, I'll be
bamboozled!

09:23.014 --> 09:25.011
Cuff him!

09:25.013 --> 09:29.008
You got the right
to remain silent, buddy.

09:30.014 --> 09:32.010
[Buzzing]

09:35.027 --> 09:37.001
Hello? Powerpuff Girls.

09:37.003 --> 09:38.028
Professor: Blossom,
it's the professor.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.017
Oh, hi.
How are you doing?

09:41.019 --> 09:44.008
Look, I'm in jail.
I've been arrested for stealing!

09:44.010 --> 09:45.010
Oh. Uh...

09:45.012 --> 09:47.008
Blossom,
are you there?

09:47.010 --> 09:48.013
Yes.

09:48.015 --> 09:50.007
Listen, I need you down
here.
I'm scared.

09:50.009 --> 09:51.013
They're asking me
questions,

09:51.015 --> 09:53.003
waving badges,
and pointing fingers.

09:53.005 --> 09:55.008
I didn't do anything.
I'm innocent!

09:55.010 --> 09:58.002
Blossom! Blossom!
Blossom!

09:58.004 --> 10:00.021
[Clinking and clanking]

10:03.024 --> 10:04.024
Ah.

10:04.026 --> 10:08.004
My masterpiece
is complete.

10:08.006 --> 10:10.017
Happy Father's Day,
my captain.

10:10.019 --> 10:13.024
I wish you were here
to enjoy--

10:13.026 --> 10:16.006
Aaaahhhhh!

10:16.008 --> 10:19.006
[Mojo shouts
indistinctly]

10:22.028 --> 10:24.002
[All gasp]

10:24.004 --> 10:25.019
It's Blossom!

10:25.021 --> 10:26.028
Look, I can explain
everything.

10:27.000 --> 10:29.002
The professor
shouldn't be in jail

10:29.004 --> 10:30.010
for stealing any golf clubs.

10:30.012 --> 10:33.013
It was Mojo's fault.
He sold them to me!

10:33.015 --> 10:36.003
[Muffled shouting]

10:36.005 --> 10:37.024
I didn't know
they were stolen!

10:37.026 --> 10:41.008
I say, Chief, we've made
a terrible mistake.

10:41.010 --> 10:45.003
Wait a minute. Blossom, you told
me you found those clubs.

10:45.005 --> 10:46.019
Which is it?
Did you find them,

10:46.021 --> 10:47.028
or did he sell them
to you?

10:48.000 --> 10:49.029
Come on, Blossom.
Tell the truth.

10:50.001 --> 10:52.020
Bubbles: Yeah,
you big, fat liar!

10:54.005 --> 10:56.012
Come on!

10:57.011 --> 11:01.012
Just tell the truth,
Blossom, please.

11:02.028 --> 11:03.026
Aaaaahhh!

11:03.028 --> 11:04.023
Watch out!

11:04.025 --> 11:06.014
Bubbles:
She's getting away!

11:06.016 --> 11:09.014
Get back here
and quit lying!

11:09.016 --> 11:11.022
Aaaahhhh!

11:11.024 --> 11:19.024
♪

11:19.026 --> 11:27.026
♪

11:27.028 --> 11:30.005
All right, all right,
all right!

11:30.007 --> 11:33.019
I did it.
I stole the clubs.

11:33.021 --> 11:35.011
Why, Blossom?

11:35.013 --> 11:37.015
Because you wanted them
so much.

11:37.017 --> 11:41.022
I just wanted to
make you happy.

11:41.024 --> 11:43.015
It's my fault.

11:43.017 --> 11:47.021
Oh, I put too much value in
a material item

11:47.023 --> 11:50.013
instead of the love of
you girls.

11:50.015 --> 11:52.010
That's what drove me
to crime.

11:52.012 --> 11:55.012
Oh, Mayor,
please go easy on Blossom.

11:55.014 --> 11:57.014
She's sorry.
Aren't you, honey?

11:57.016 --> 11:58.019
Yeah.

11:58.021 --> 12:01.021
What do you say, Chief?
It is her first offense.

12:01.023 --> 12:04.015
It is very sad.

12:06.001 --> 12:07.026
But the law is the law!

12:07.028 --> 12:09.014
Narrator: Blossom was sentenced

12:09.016 --> 12:11.019
to 200 hours of
community service.

12:11.021 --> 12:13.019
This was a harsh reminder
to her and to all

12:13.021 --> 12:15.011
that crime does not pay.

12:15.013 --> 12:17.007
Boy, you can say that again.

12:17.009 --> 12:19.003
Voice: Crime
does not pay.
What?

12:19.005 --> 12:21.007
Well, it doesn't.

12:21.009 --> 12:23.021
Narrator: Once again,
the day is saved

12:23.023 --> 12:26.018
thanks to
the Powerpuff Girls!

12:26.020 --> 12:29.013
Well, two of them, at least.

12:29.015 --> 12:34.015
♪

12:36.019 --> 12:45.018
♪

12:47.022 --> 12:49.003
Narrator:
The city of Townsville--

12:49.005 --> 12:52.009
a city where
villainy exists 24-7.

12:52.011 --> 12:53.015
But don't be alarmed,

12:53.017 --> 12:57.010
for the Powerpuff Girls always
spring into action.

12:57.012 --> 13:00.008
Rarrrrrrr!

13:00.010 --> 13:09.022
♪

13:09.024 --> 13:13.029
Face it--these girls
will clean their clocks.

13:14.001 --> 13:16.001
[Alarm ringing]

13:20.002 --> 13:23.029
Watch as they wind up
the crime every time!

13:24.001 --> 13:28.017
♪

13:28.019 --> 13:31.001
[Mooing]

13:31.003 --> 13:37.015
♪

13:37.017 --> 13:38.029
It's a lucky stroke for us

13:39.001 --> 13:43.000
that these are no secondhand
heroines that keep our city safe

13:43.002 --> 13:45.028
deep into the night and into
the wee hours of the morning.

13:46.000 --> 13:47.018
And on a school night, even.

13:47.020 --> 13:49.009
Speaking of school...

13:49.011 --> 13:53.011
Class, can you tell me what
this is a picture of?

13:53.013 --> 13:54.012
Class: Ball!

13:54.014 --> 13:56.029
Very good!
And this is a...

13:57.001 --> 13:58.011
Dog!

13:58.013 --> 14:01.000
Very good.
And this is a...

14:01.002 --> 14:05.001
A 4-stroke internal
combustion engine!

14:05.003 --> 14:08.000
Very good.
And this is a...

14:08.002 --> 14:09.019
is--is a...

14:09.021 --> 14:12.010
[Loud snoring]

14:30.026 --> 14:33.000
George Washington!
Pi R squared!
Borscht!

14:33.002 --> 14:35.006
Ha ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha ha!

14:35.008 --> 14:37.025
It's nice of you
to join us, girls.

14:37.027 --> 14:41.025
This is the third time this week
you've fallen asleep in class.

14:41.027 --> 14:43.021
We're sorry,
Ms. Keane.

14:43.023 --> 14:45.000
We can't help it.

14:45.002 --> 14:46.027
We wouldn't be so tired

14:46.029 --> 14:48.011
if we weren't out
every single night...

14:48.013 --> 14:51.000
Keeping Townsville
safe from crime

14:51.002 --> 14:52.021
for you
and its citizens.

14:52.023 --> 14:55.002
Hmm. Yes.
Well, that's true.

14:55.004 --> 14:56.019
I did forget
that part.

14:56.021 --> 14:58.013
But that does not
excuse you

14:58.015 --> 15:01.011
from your responsibilities
at school.

15:01.013 --> 15:02.025
You're right.

15:02.027 --> 15:03.028
We're sorry.

15:04.000 --> 15:06.009
It'll never happen again.

15:06.011 --> 15:09.000
[Loud snoring]

15:10.029 --> 15:15.010
No, it won't.
It certainly won't.

15:16.017 --> 15:18.013
Narrator:
Later that day...

15:18.015 --> 15:21.021
Oh, hello, girls.
Home from school so...

15:21.023 --> 15:25.027
Jumping Jehoshaphat!
What the heck is that?!

15:25.029 --> 15:29.022
♪

15:29.024 --> 15:33.008
Parent-teacher conference?!

15:33.010 --> 15:42.011
Nooooooooooo!

15:43.007 --> 15:45.026
[Woman sobbing]

15:48.002 --> 15:49.019
You're next,
Professor.

15:49.021 --> 15:51.002
[Gulps]

15:55.005 --> 15:58.002
Please have a seat.

15:59.012 --> 16:02.022
Oops. Uh, sorry.
Ha ha!

16:38.022 --> 16:41.019
Well...
I didn't do it!

16:41.021 --> 16:44.020
Um, you needed to speak
to me about the girls?

16:44.022 --> 16:47.010
Yes, Professor.
I'm very concerned.

16:47.012 --> 16:49.008
They've been falling
asleep in class,

16:49.010 --> 16:51.017
and their participation
is slipping.

16:51.019 --> 16:54.012
Well, what do you suppose
the reason is, Ms. Keane?

16:54.014 --> 16:58.003
I believe all of this late-night
crimefighting is to blame.

16:58.005 --> 17:00.016
Well, they are
superheroes, you know,

17:00.018 --> 17:03.005
and saving the world's
a big responsibility.

17:03.007 --> 17:06.003
But education is
a bigger responsibility.

17:06.005 --> 17:10.026
Yep, that am true, Ms. Keane,
but what do you propose?

17:10.028 --> 17:14.021
Well, I suggest
you set a curfew.

17:15.013 --> 17:17.024
Girls: A curfew?!
But, Professor...

17:17.026 --> 17:21.001
No buts, girls.
You're to be home by 7:30.

17:21.003 --> 17:22.019
Girls: 7:30?!

17:22.021 --> 17:26.011
But the juicy stuff doesn't even
start until at least 9:00!

17:26.013 --> 17:29.029
7:30 isn't as dark
as 9:00, though.

17:30.001 --> 17:31.008
[Buzzing]

17:31.010 --> 17:33.018
The hotline!
Professor, we gotta go!

17:33.020 --> 17:36.007
Girls, don't
forget--7:30.

17:36.009 --> 17:38.009
Girls: We won't.

17:38.029 --> 17:47.004
♪

17:47.006 --> 17:49.002
[People screaming]

17:49.004 --> 17:50.013
Aaahhhh!

17:50.015 --> 17:53.017
Narrator: Mojo Jojo is turning
Townsville into Swiss cheese!

17:53.019 --> 17:55.000
Look sharp, everyone!

17:55.002 --> 17:57.020
It's the Powerpuff Girls
here to save us!

17:57.022 --> 17:59.001
Narrator:
You said it, Jack!

17:59.003 --> 18:03.025
It'll be a "bries" for our girls
to cream that "muenster" Mojo.

18:03.027 --> 18:07.002
Things aren't looking too gouda
for you, Mojo,

18:07.004 --> 18:10.002
so leave that prov alone
and prepare to be shredded!

18:10.004 --> 18:18.003
♪

18:18.005 --> 18:23.019
Girls, it's 7:30!
Time to come in now!

18:23.021 --> 18:25.004
Girls: Awwwwww!

18:25.006 --> 18:27.019
Sorry, Mojo,
but we've gotta go.

18:27.021 --> 18:30.006
We've got school
in the morning.

18:30.008 --> 18:33.018
Yeah. We've got to be
in bed by 7:30.

18:33.020 --> 18:34.019
Professor: Girls!

18:34.021 --> 18:36.004
Girls: Coming, Professor!

18:36.006 --> 18:38.025
Narrator: Now what will happen
to Townsville

18:38.027 --> 18:41.010
without its heroes
to protect it?

18:41.021 --> 18:44.027
Oh, I camembert to watch!

18:44.029 --> 18:45.029
Girls: But--

18:46.001 --> 18:47.011
No buts, girls.

18:47.013 --> 18:48.019
You've got school
in the morning,

18:48.021 --> 18:49.027
and you need
your rest.

18:49.029 --> 18:51.014
But what about
Townsville?

18:51.016 --> 18:52.028
Townsville's fine.

18:53.000 --> 18:56.022
Oh, just look at it--
so quiet, so peaceful.

18:56.024 --> 19:00.007
Thanks to you, Townsville's as
safe as safe can be.

19:00.009 --> 19:02.008
So you shut
those sleepy eyes

19:02.010 --> 19:06.012
and hop aboard
the dreamland express.

19:06.014 --> 19:08.028
Hop aboard
the dreamland express!

19:09.004 --> 19:10.005
That's better.

19:10.007 --> 19:11.029
Good night, girls.

19:12.001 --> 19:14.018
[Door squeaks,
then closes]

19:16.021 --> 19:18.002
[Rumbling]

19:18.004 --> 19:19.002
You hear that?

19:19.004 --> 19:21.012
[Marching footsteps]

19:21.014 --> 19:27.010
♪

19:27.012 --> 19:33.010
♪

19:33.012 --> 19:34.015
Oh, no! It's...

19:34.017 --> 19:35.009
A parade!

19:35.011 --> 19:37.001
Not just any
parade, Bubbles,

19:37.003 --> 19:39.003
but a parade
of villainy.

19:39.005 --> 19:41.016
And it's marching straight
into Townsville!

19:41.018 --> 19:42.027
Professor!

19:42.029 --> 19:44.024
Go to bed, girls!

19:44.026 --> 19:47.013
Oh, this makes me
sick to my stomach.

19:47.015 --> 19:48.022
What are
we going to do?

19:48.024 --> 19:51.014
There's nothing we <i>can</i><i>do</i>
except try to go to sleep

19:51.016 --> 19:54.016
and hope that Townsville is
still there in the morning.

19:54.018 --> 19:56.024
That's it?
The parade's over?

19:56.026 --> 19:58.009
Where's the floats?

19:58.011 --> 20:01.025
Where's the giant 3-D cartoon
character endorsement balloons?

20:01.027 --> 20:03.021
Rarrrrrrr!
Eee!

20:03.023 --> 20:05.013
Girls: Professor!

20:05.015 --> 20:07.024
Professor: Go to sleep!

20:07.026 --> 20:10.019
[Hotline buzzing]

20:12.019 --> 20:15.009
Yes, Mayor? Okay.
We'll be right th--

20:15.011 --> 20:16.015
Uh, no, thanks.

20:16.017 --> 20:18.005
We're not interested in
buying the paper. Thank you.

20:18.007 --> 20:20.028
[Electricity crackling]

20:21.000 --> 20:22.026
Good night, girls.

20:22.028 --> 20:26.000
Ahhhhh.

20:35.005 --> 20:36.016
[Jazz playing]

20:36.018 --> 20:37.026
Ahhhhh.

20:37.028 --> 20:40.009
We interrupt this program
for this special bulletin.

20:40.011 --> 20:41.028
Townsville is
under attack!

20:42.000 --> 20:46.004
[Voice slowing]
We need the Power--

20:49.000 --> 20:50.028
[Lion roaring]

20:54.003 --> 20:55.015
Ahhhhh.

20:55.017 --> 20:59.008
TV announcer: We interrupt this
program for this special report.

20:59.010 --> 21:01.011
Help! Townsville's
burning down,

21:01.013 --> 21:04.001
and the Powerpuff Girls
are nowhere in sight!

21:04.003 --> 21:05.021
Things are looking--

21:05.023 --> 21:07.008
♪ Ah ♪

21:07.010 --> 21:09.003
Whew.

21:09.005 --> 21:10.015
Townsville's
being eaten!

21:10.017 --> 21:12.011
Townsville's
being invaded!

21:12.013 --> 21:15.028
Man: Rioting! Mayhem!
Utter annihilation!

21:16.000 --> 21:17.018
Man #2: <i>El muerte!</i>

21:17.020 --> 21:18.024
Sonny Dial: Welcome to
the time channel,

21:18.026 --> 21:21.014
where we give you
up-to-the-minute time

21:21.016 --> 21:23.010
24 hours a day.

21:23.012 --> 21:25.007
Up next,
the current time.

21:25.009 --> 21:27.009
Hello. I'm Sonny Dial,

21:27.011 --> 21:29.003
here to bring you
the latest time.

21:29.005 --> 21:31.009
But first, I hope
all of you remembered

21:31.011 --> 21:33.009
that last night was
daylight savings,

21:33.011 --> 21:37.022
which means everyone sets their
clocks back by one hour.

21:37.024 --> 21:40.012
That makes
our current time 6:41.

21:40.014 --> 21:45.018
I'll be back at 6:42 with
the up-to-the-minute time.

21:49.012 --> 21:52.025
Crikey! I forgot to
set the clocks back!

21:52.027 --> 21:53.026
Girls, wake up.

21:53.028 --> 21:55.007
Girls, wake up!

21:55.009 --> 21:57.028
Buzz! Buzz! Buzz!
Buzz! Buzz!

21:58.000 --> 21:59.005
Get out of bed, now!

21:59.007 --> 22:00.017
Daylight savings.
Clocks wrong.

22:00.019 --> 22:02.010
45 minutes.
Save Townsville now!

22:02.012 --> 22:03.018
But what about
our curfew?

22:03.020 --> 22:06.010
No time.
Go! Go! Go!

22:06.012 --> 22:08.024
[Panting]

22:12.012 --> 22:15.014
...and so in a flurry
of Powerpuffery,

22:15.016 --> 22:19.019
the city of Townsville seems to
be getting back to normal.

22:19.021 --> 22:21.000
Townsville saved
once again.

22:21.002 --> 22:22.025
-A-okay.
-Peachy keen.

22:22.027 --> 22:23.025
-Jim-dandy.
-Okey-dokey.

22:23.027 --> 22:27.004
<i>iMuy bueno!</i>
<i>iViva la Powerpuff!</i>

22:27.006 --> 22:30.011
Ah, them's my girls.

22:30.013 --> 22:33.019
Narrator: It sure is nice to
have the girls to fall back on,

22:33.021 --> 22:34.028
eh, Professor?

22:35.000 --> 22:38.024
And so once again
the day is saved thanks to...

22:38.026 --> 22:40.024
Benjamin Franklin's suggestion
of setting clocks back

22:40.026 --> 22:42.006
during the winter
for extra daylight

22:42.008 --> 22:43.025
to conserve economic spending
on candles

22:43.027 --> 22:47.003
and the Powerpuff Girls!

